  "description": [
    "Now that it is all over theres no harm in admitting the fact that the Trustees of the Internal Improvement Fund were severely jolted by the de feat of the drainage amendment They were placed in an embarrassing position because the loss of the money they expected to derive from the special tax brought them face to face with a dilemma which as usual had two horns 3 Horn No 1 was to stop the work tie up the finished dredge and sus pend building operations on the unfinished one Horn No 2 was to sell the public lands in their charge at the low prices offered for overflowed lands and keep the work going on Either one of these horns looked wicked enough to scare the average of ficial with a sacred trust to perform for the correct discharge of which he was responsible to his conscience and to the people And the Trustees gave the dilemma much anxious thought as they looked at the two horns presented to them If they took hold of the first and abandoned the work they would have the consciousness of duty unperformed They are directed by law to carry on the work"
  ],
